; PMGRE.DEF -- cWarp clone of PMGRE.DLL (pure forwarder to PMMERGE)
; Auto-generated from the original OrigFiles\PMGRE.DLL LX export table.
; The original PMGRE.DLL (2231 bytes) contains ZERO code: all 78 exports
; are LX forwarders into PMMERGE.DLL (the merged graphics engine).
;
; MUST be built with IBM LINK386 -- OpenWatcom wlink cannot emit LX forwarders.
; LINK386 forwarder syntax (verified vs DDK sample DEFs): 'name = MODULE.targetordinal'
;   - NO '#' before the ordinal.
;   - NO local '@ordinal' -- LINK386 does not accept one on a forwarder (auto-assigned).
; NOTE: exports are therefore by-NAME with auto ordinals, NOT the original ordinals. If any
; importer uses PMGRE by ordinal (DDK drivers do, e.g. '=PMGRE.37'), this clone would need
; full ordinal parity -> use the runtime-thunk approach (wlink: IMPORT PMMERGE.n + EXPORT
; name.ord = thunk) instead.

